  "text": "From E16-E17, formation of the metabolically-inactive cornified layer results in acquisition of a highly competent barrier that prevents water loss, entry of toxins, and microbial invasion. At this stage, periderm disaggregates in a patterned manner that recapitulates barrier formation due to loss of contact with the terminally-differentiated keratinocytes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] (Fig. 2) .",
